&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Cloud Alliance Manager, you will lead and expand our Global Strategic Partnership with key Cloud Providers. In this role, you will be responsible for driving joint go-to-market initiatives, deepening technical integrations, executing agreements, and maximizing revenue opportunities through programs and sales motions. This position requires a highly strategic and execution-focused leader with a deep understanding of the cloud ecosystem, cloud technologies, and partner management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;At Datadog, we place value in our office culture - the relationships and collaboration it builds and the creativity it brings to the table. We operate as a hybrid workplace to ensure our Datadogs can create a work-life harmony that best fits them.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Revenue Growth: Identify and execute joint business opportunities, including marketplace transactions, co-selling initiatives, and Cloud funding programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go-to-Market Leadership: Collaborate with Cloud Providers and internal teams (sales, marketing, and product) to develop and launch integrated solutions, campaigns, and enablement programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical &amp;amp; Product Alignment with GTM and Sales Plays: Work closely with Datadog’s product and engineering teams to promote Cloud integrations and ensure technical alignment with Cloud services.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Field &amp;amp; Partner Enablement: Train and support Datadog’s sales teams on Cloud partnership benefits, co-sell motions, and marketplace offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure &amp;amp; Optimize: Track partnership performance using key metrics (pipeline, revenue and incentives) and continuously refine strategy to maximize impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in 7+ years of partner-facing business development, strategic alliances, or channel sales at a cloud services or software as a service organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in driving sales, partner sourced and partner influenced opportunities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to quickly understand technical concepts and explain them to others verbally and in writing&lt;/li&gt;
