&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do as a Solutions Engineer Manager, Associate Programs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role: Impacting the Future of Cloudflare&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Manager for Cloudflare’s Associate Engineer (ASE) Program, you aren&#39;t just managing a team; you are architecting the engine that powers our technical field organization. Your mission is to design, execute, and scale a world-class development program that transforms early-career talent into high-performing technical consultants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a curriculum builder and talent strategist first. You will lead a cohort of ASEs (Interns) through a rigorous, multi-modal journey—blending deep technical networking knowledge with sharp commercial acumen. You will bridge the gap between &quot;knowing the tech&quot; and &quot;solving the customer&#39;s business problem,&quot; ensuring our graduates are ready to hit the ground running in Solutions Engineering, Customer Success, and beyond. You will be the main decision maker on Interns that succeed into a full time role as well.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Program Architecture: Own the end-to-end ASE lifecycle, from onboarding and curriculum design to &quot;graduation&quot; into the field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pedagogical Leadership: Build hands-on labs, certification paths, and competency-based assessments that validate both technical depth (Cloud, Security, Workers) and soft skills (Discovery, Demoing, MEDDPICC).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder Alignment: Act as the primary liaison between University Recruiting, Sales Leadership, and Global Enablement to ensure the program&#39;s output aligns with the business&#39;s hiring needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coaching &amp;amp; Mentorship: Provide direct management to a cohort of ASEs, offering structured feedback, career pathing, and performance coaching.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operational Excellence: Track and report on program KPIs, such as &quot;Time to Productivity,&quot; graduation rates, and long-term retention of program alumni.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Culture Catalyst: Instill Cloudflare’s values of curiosity and collaboration into our newest team members, setting the tone for their entire career.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify best capability and align ASEs accordingly by working with respective leaders (Solution Engineer roles, BDR roles, Customer Success..etc)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements: What You Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in Technical Enablement, Program Management, or customer-facing technical roles (SE, SA, or Professional Services).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Program Design Mastery: Proven track record of building and managing &quot;Academy-style&quot; programs or large-scale technical training initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Fluency: 3+ years of experience with Internet protocols (TCP/IP, DNS, TLS), Cloud Security, or Edge Computing. You should be able to &quot;talk shop&quot; with engineers while teaching a beginner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Instructional Mindset: You don&#39;t just know the material; you know how to &lt;em&gt;teach&lt;/em&gt; it. You have experience creating structured learning paths and hands-on lab environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder Influence: Ability to navigate a complex global organization and gain buy-in from senior Sales and Engineering leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership: 2+ years of experience managing teams or leading high-impact cross-functional projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sales Literacy: Familiarity with modern sales methodologies (e.g., MEDDPICC, Command of the Message) and the ability to weave these into a technical curriculum.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
